'''Baresmanas''' ({{lang-el|{{lang|grc|Βαρεσμανᾶς}}}}) was an eminent [[Sassanian]] [[Persian people|Persian]] general. He is known only from his participation in the [[Battle of Dara]] in 530 against the [[Byzantine]]s led by [[Belisarius]], recorded by [[Procopius of Caesarea]]. In this battle, Baresmanas was the second-in-command of the Persian army under [[Perozes]], and was killed during the fight by [[Sunicas]]. According to the account of Procopius, he was one-eyed.
